history.text: Hello!
Hey!
What do you think about the movie?
Sounds interesting, it is a comedy that uses animals as the main characters
Do you know what it is called?
I believe it is Zootopia, however I have not seen the movie, so I can not be entirely sure
Do they explain the setting?
It takes place in a rural bunnyburrow
It's directed by Byron Howard and Rich Moore, have you ever seen a movie by them?
I'm not sure.  I am not very familiar with directors of films.
Can you tell me about the plot?
The film looks at a rabbit cop and this dealings with the a con artist
I like movies with odd pairings.
The suspect, Otterton, is recorded confessing to tax evasion. The police catch up to him and think they have him, when he banishes.
Is the main character a male or female?
The officer is female while the suspect is male.
Is the ending given away?
Yes, the adventure continues with the officer finding an underground prison that the wolves keep people in.
Would you like to hear the ending?
Yes please
Spoiler Alert: Judy, the officer, solves the case while finding the con man being held by the wolves.  Judy and the con man become friends as escape from the prison.
That sounds like a happy ending
However, in a press confrence her comments cause tension between wolf a prey so she is forced to quit! I guess the was not the ending and the saga continues.
Oh i see.  It is a plot twist!
I would be interested in seeing this movie.
Judy and the otter, find a drug making Ram who is stealing tulips to source the drug
This movie is pretty intense and they throw in comedy along the way!
Having the characters as animals makes the movie sound like a movie for kids, but it sounds like it involves drugs and abductions!
I think we are actually at the end now, and there is a twist. Should I hold off on saying it?
Go ahead!
The Mayor, Bellwether, was behind most of the crimes that occured! Judy tapes him confessing it to her, while he tries to pin everything on her
The police department ends up arresting the mayor.
Wow it sounds like a big conspiracy!
I agree, seems like a lot for a kids movie. Seems like a very interesting movie overall!
I agree!

uid1response.feedback: The other user explains the main plot points of the movie to make it sound dramatic and fun and intense and that sounds like a movie I would watch.
